'''Douglas Neville Daft''' [[Companion of the Order of Australia|AC]] (born 20 March 1943 in [[Cessnock, New South Wales]]) is an Australian businessman.

He graduated from the [[University of New England, Australia|University of New England]] in [[Armidale, New South Wales|Armidale]], [[New South Wales]] in 1963 with a [[Bachelor of Arts]] degree, majoring in [[Mathematics]]. While at the [[University of New England, Australia|University of New England]] he lived at Robb College.  During the 1960s he taught science at [[Vaucluse High School|Vaucluse Boys' High School]] in [[Sydney]]. In 1970 he graduated from the [[University of New South Wales]] with a Diploma of Admin.<ref>{{cite web |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091112021409/http://www.business.unsw.edu.au/nps/servlet/portalservice?GI_ID=System.LoggedOutInheritableArea&maxWnd=_Alumni_MeetAlumniLeaders_DouglasDaft |publisher=[[UNSW Sydney]] |url=http://www.business.unsw.edu.au/nps/servlet/portalservice?GI_ID=System.LoggedOutInheritableArea&maxWnd=_Alumni_MeetAlumniLeaders_DouglasDaft |archive-date=12 November 2009 |title=Douglas Daft AC |work=Meet our alumni leaders; Australian School of Business |accessdate=16 June 2017 |date=9 September 2009 |deadurl=yes |df=dmy-all }}</ref> He was CEO of [[Coca-Cola]] (2000–2004).<ref>{{cite news |title=New Coca-Cola boss has Aussie links |work=[[Sydney Morning Herald]] |date=6 May 2004 |page=23 }}</ref> In 2005, he was appointed Companion of the [[Order of Australia]] (AC) for his leadership in the global business community. He is currently a Corporate Director of [[Wal-Mart]] and on the Advisory Board of the Front Row Group of Companies Ltd.

Douglas Daft now is advisor for [[NM Rothschild and Sons|Rothschild]] and sits on the Board of Trustees for preeminent [[Thunderbird School of Global Management]].

