{{Infobox video game |title = |image = M.U.D. TV coverart.png |caption = |developer = [[Realmforge Studios]] |publisher = [[Kalypso Media]] |producer = |designer = |engine = |released = February 23, 2010<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/m-u-d--tv-new-pics-released-of-kalyso-s-tv-studio-sim|title=M.U.D. TV press release|date=December 1, 2009|publisher=Games Industry|accessdate=17 December 2009}}</ref> |genre = [[Business simulation game|Business simulation]] |modes = [[Single-player]], [[Multiplayer video game|Multiplayer]], [[Cooperative gameplay|Cooperative multiplayer]] |platforms = [[Microsoft Windows]] }}
'''''M.U.D. TV''''' ('''''Mad Ugly Dirty TV''''') is a [[Business simulation game|business simulation]] video game developed by [[Realmforge Studios]] and published by [[Kalypso Media]] for [[Microsoft Windows]] released on February 23, 2010. The game is centered on running a multi-media broadcasting business. The game is meant as a parody of many modern news stations.
In January 2011, [[Steam (software)|Steam]] offered the clients that pre-ordered the game ''[[Dungeons (video game)|Dungeons]]'', another game from the same publisher, a free copy of ''M.U.D. TV''.
==Reception== The Australian video game talk show ''[[Good Game (television series)|Good Game]]'''s two reviewers gave the game a 6/10 and 8/10.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/tv/goodgame/stories/s2895412.htm |title=Good Game stories - M.U.D. TV| publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation| date=2010-05-10}}</ref>
The [[Metacritic]] website has a global score of 53, based on 6 reviews.<ref>http://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/mud-tv/critic-reviews</ref> The best review was from PC Games (Germany), which reviewed it 78%.<ref>http://www.pcgames.de/Mud-TV-PC-232979/Tests/MUD-TV-im-Test-Altbackene-WiSim-oder-gute-Mad-TV-Hommage-705520/</ref><ref>http://www.golem.de/1003/73744.html</ref>
