{{infobox officeholder |name= Sayeed Khokon |native_name= সাঈদ খোকন |image= Sayeed Khokon.jpg |caption= Sayeed Khokon at Digital World 2016 |office= Mayor of [[Dhaka South City Corporation|Dhaka South]] |term_start= 2015 |birth_date= {{birth date and age|1970|6|19}} |birth_place= | father = [[Mohammad Hanif (mayor)|Mohammad Hanif]] | residence = Dhaka |nationality = Bangladeshi | party = [[Bangladesh Awami League]] |occupation= businessman, politician | known_for = Mayor of [[Dhaka South City Corporation]] |website={{URL|www.sayeedkhokon.com}} }}
'''Sayeed Khokon''' (born 19 June 1970)<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sayeedkhokon.com/biography.php |title=SAYEED KHOKON - Story of Sayeed Khokon |publisher=sayeedkhokon.com |accessdate=28 August 2015}}</ref> is a [[Bangladesh]]i businessman, politician and current mayor of [[Dhaka South City Corporation]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Awami League-backed Sayeed Khokon emulates father, wins Dhaka South City mayor election |url=http://bdnews24.com/bangladesh/2015/04/29/awami-league-backed-sayeed-khokon-emulates-father-wins-dhaka-south-city-mayor-election |newspaper=[[bdnews24.com]] |date=29 April 2015 |accessdate=28 August 2015}}</ref> He is the son of Dhaka city's first mayor Late [[Mohammad Hanif (mayor)]].
==Mayor election== He won in the first Dhaka South City Corporation election on 29 April 2015.
